                            <comment id="12409967" author="oliver.heger@t-online.de" created="Mon, 8 Aug 2005 01:38:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree that the current implementation is inconsistent.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should be no problem that XML elements occurring in the loaded configuration&lt;br/&gt;
document but don&apos;t have text are added to the configuration. To use your example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;configuration&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;foo&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;bar/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/foo&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/configuration&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If this file was loaded, conf.containsKey(&quot;foo.bar&quot;) should return true and&lt;br/&gt;
conf.getString(&quot;foo.bar&quot;) should return an empty string, right?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What about the &amp;lt;foo&amp;gt; element? ATM the &quot;foo&quot; key is not contained in the&lt;br/&gt;
configuration object. For the sake of consistency the same results should be&lt;br/&gt;
returned as for the &quot;foo.bar&quot; key. Do you agree?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While this is only a minor change in the source code it will have a major&lt;br/&gt;
impact. The number of keys in an XMLConfiguration would increase, which might&lt;br/&gt;
break existing code using this class. What do others think about this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12409968" author="oliver.heger@t-online.de" created="Sun, 21 Aug 2005 03:23:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;XMLConfiguration was updated to deal with empty elements. These elements appear&lt;br/&gt;
now in a configuration with a value of an empty string. This also includes&lt;br/&gt;
elements whose value is only a comment or whitespace. Not included are elements&lt;br/&gt;
without text content, but with child elements.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12409969" author="e.lacazedieu@lectra.com" created="Mon, 29 Aug 2005 15:24:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry that I did not answer to the first message : I was on holidays the past 3&lt;br/&gt;
weeks.&lt;br/&gt;
The behaviour described in the second comment is exactly what I was expecting.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks a lot.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Etienne Lacazedieu&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
